424
00:26:53,868 --> 00:26:56,132
<i>what would happen to
the technology of today?</i>

425
00:26:56,270 --> 00:26:58,795
<i>What would happen to the electric car?</i>

426
00:26:59,173 --> 00:27:04,270
<i>It all came down to a decisive meeting
at California's Air Resources Board.</i>

427
00:27:04,545 --> 00:27:07,378
<i>Citizens and industry alike</i>

428
00:27:07,448 --> 00:27:11,111
<i>testified as CARB prepared to
vote on the fate of the electric car.</i>

429
00:27:11,219 --> 00:27:14,245
<i>I'd also like to thank
all the other stakeholders,</i>

430
00:27:14,322 --> 00:27:17,450
<i>particularly also,
the auto industry</i>

431
00:27:17,525 --> 00:27:20,551
<i>who is going to have a major impact here.</i>

432
00:27:20,895 --> 00:27:24,422
<i>I like the fact that
hydrogen might be in a position</i>

433
00:27:24,499 --> 00:27:28,435
<i>to displace the petroleum products.</i>

434
00:27:28,536 --> 00:27:31,733
<i>I share your optimism on fuel cells,
just not to the extent.</i>

435
00:27:31,806 --> 00:27:36,243
<i>I think it's a bait and switch
