01:24:55,179 --> 01:24:58,910
but there's a chance that they might be able
to have something to do with one another

1303
01:24:58,983 --> 01:25:00,314
in a positive way.

1304
01:25:00,384 --> 01:25:05,185
And that's where I think that the
plug-in hybrid is the natural next step,

1305
01:25:05,489 --> 01:25:07,719
<i>and that it is avilable to us today.</i>

1306
01:25:08,492 --> 01:25:10,517
<i>This is a plug-in hybrid Prius,</i>

1307
01:25:10,595 --> 01:25:14,656
which is a modification
to a normal Toyota Prius

1308
01:25:14,732 --> 01:25:17,166
that allows you to travel...

1309
01:25:17,234 --> 01:25:21,364
<i>Which gives you up to
150-180 miles per gallon</i>

1310
01:25:21,439 --> 01:25:23,463
<i>for the first 50 to 60 miles of the day.</i>

1311
01:25:24,275 --> 01:25:27,403
<i>We don't need an expensive
charging infrastructure to use this car.</i>

1312
01:25:27,478 --> 01:25:29,742
<i>You can just plug it in
anywhere in your garage.</i>

1313
01:25:29,814 --> 01:25:32,977
So we make the environmentalists
happy because it's cleaner.

1314
01:25:33,050 --> 01:25:38,317
We make the neo-conservatives
happy because it uses less gasoline.

1315
01:25:38,389 --> 01:25:40,880
Well, everyone's happy
because it uses less gasoline.

1316
01:25:40,958 --> 01:25:44,951
<i>Plugging in could go a long way to
reducing our dependence on oil.</i>

1317
01:25:46,330 --> 01:25:49,595
<i>And generating that electricity
with the wind and the sun</i>

1318
01:25:49,667 --> 01:25:52,227
<i>would create even less pollution.</i>

1319
01:25:52,903 --> 01:25:57,931
<i>With his battery technology in most
